Class ControllerItemClientRow

java.lang.Object
proiect.ControllerItemClientRow
public class ControllerItemClientRow extends Object
The ControllerItemClientRow class represents a JavaFX controller for managing a client row in the user interface. It handles the display and interaction logic for client-related data within a given row.

  • Field Details

    • clientName

      javafx.scene.text.Text clientName
      Represents a JavaFX Text element used to display the name of a client. This field is part of the user interface managed by the ControllerItemClientRow class. It can display and update the client's name dynamically in the application.

      void initialize()

    • showClientDetails

      public void showClientDetails(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent) throws SQLException, IOException
      Displays the details of a client in the user interface by updating relevant elements in the main controller. This method is triggered by a mouse event and interacts with the main controller to set up client-specific data.
      Parameters:
      mouseEvent - the mouse event that triggers this method; typically associated with a user action such as clicking on a client row
      Throws:
      SQLException - if a database access error occurs
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs during processing
